      "side": 1,
      "message": "In each of your Test functions, it appears that the matcher stays the same for all cases. That is good organization, IMO. As a result, I think you should omit matcher from the struct and build it in the test loop.\n\nfollow-up suggestion: if you omit matcher, there are only two inputs and one output, so I would encourage use of a test helper function instead of a list of test cases.",
